               <person>
                  <persName role="owner" ref="PRS0000">ʿAmda Śǝllāse is mentioned as the commissioner on <locus target="129rb">129rb</locus>, but his name has been written, in vivid red and in a secondary hand, over an erasure. The original owner of the Ms. might be Walda ʾAmlāk whose name has been retained on <locus target="107rb">107rb</locus>.&#xD;
The name of the commissioner and his family members have been written over erased names in the supplication formulas: ʿAmda Śǝllāse (e.g., <locus target="3ra">3ra</locus>c, 6rabc, 7vc, 21va, 26rb, 30vabc, 94rab), his wife Walatta Hāymānot (<locus target="90vc">90vc</locus>, 92rc, 94rab), Ḫǝdrä Mikāʾel (<locus target="19rb">19rb</locus>, 21rc, 21vb, 95va), Gabra Śǝllāse (<locus target="90va">90va</locus>, 92rc), Walda Śǝllāse (Ba-Gäday) (<locus target="90vc">90vc</locus>, 96rb, 99rbc),  ʾƎqwǝba Mikāʾel (<locus target="95vb">95vb</locus>, 104ra). &#xD;
In <locus from="3r" to="90r">3r-90r</locus>, the names of Walda Mikāʾel (most frequently), Gabra Māryām and Sǝḥunä Śǝllāse have been added, in black and in another hand, over the names mentioned above.</persName>
